    desc: "Introduces students to textual culture in Islamic Africa, its libraries and current archives, discusses strategies employed by African authors to make their writings more effective in producing social and political outcomes, and analyzes texts beyond their informational surface, delving into their social and cultural contexts.",
    section: ["FREE"], rmpScore: 0
  },
  "HIS 139C": {
