    prereqs: [["HIS 100"]],
    ge: null, quarters: ["F", "W", "S"],
    desc: "Widely considered the antechamber of WWII, the Spanish Civil War (1936-1939) was the first large-scale international clash of Fascists and anti-Fascists. It was simultaneously a national conflict and a global proxy war, colonial and anti-colonial; and yet, it is often overlooked.",
