    ge: "PR-C", quarters: ["F", "W", "S"],
    desc: "This intermediate-level course engaged with poetry that incorporates unfamiliar languages, explores the aesthetics and politics of translation, and the creative possibilities (and limitations) of bilingualism. Discussions primarily conducted in English but may include Spanish lines or phrasing. Work can be completed in English, Spanish, or Spanglish.",
