    units: 5, division: "upper",
    prereqs: [],
    ge: null, quarters: ["F", "W", "S"],
    desc: "Victorian prophecy, Victorian criticism: an examination of some major writings of 19th-century nonfiction prose by Carlyle, Mill, Ruskin, Newman, Arnold, Pater, and Wilde, with a glance at the social context and the minor fictional forms of the era. Critical approach designations: Genres, Histories.",
    section: ["FREE"], rmpScore: 0
