    units: 5, division: "upper",
    prereqs: [],
    ge: "TA", quarters: ["F", "W", "S"],
    desc: "Examines the form and function of the letter in literature from antiquity to the contemporary moment. Considers all writing, from the most expressly public to the most seemingly private, as a form of correspondence, and we will contribute our own letters, in both creative and critical modes, in an effort to expand our capacities for critical analysis of texts. Critical approach designations: Genres, Media.",
    section: ["FREE"], rmpScore: 0
  },
